Description: Fragment of round handle from neck join to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown. Rectangular stamp with double cornucopia and axe symbols.
Curator's comments: Name Menothemis. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0367.05.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (188)
